text: Zhuchengtyrannus (meaning "Zhucheng tyrant") was a genus of tyrannosaurids from the Upper Cretaceous of Shandong, China. Its only species is Zhuchengtyrannus magnus. == Description == Zhuchengtyrannus, a large theropod, is estimated to be comparable in size to both Tarbosaurus and Tyrannosaurus. == References == Category:Theropods Category:Tyrannosaurids Category:Dinosaurs of China Category:Dinosaurs
